# RabbitMQ broker admin password (the Bitnami subchart's
# auth.password). ADR-057 PR-B2.5.
#
# 1. Generate a strong password (e.g., `openssl rand -base64 32`)
#    and replace this placeholder.
# 2. Save as ./secrets/rabbitmq_password.txt (the .txt suffix is
#    gitignored).
# 3. Run `make k8s-bootstrap-secrets` (which re-runs setup-vault.sh
#    + helm upgrade). The password lands at:
#    - Vault: kv/audittrace/rabbitmq/admin
#    - k8s Secret: <release>-rabbitmq (created by Bitnami subchart
#      from .Values.auth.password)
# 4. Rotation: replace the password, re-run setup-vault.sh +
#    helm upgrade.
REPLACE_WITH_STRONG_PASSWORD
